    "instruction": "Using metric.csv only, restrict to rows whose cmdb_id is one of the candidate services: [\"ts-auth-service\",\"ts-order-service\",\"ts-route-service\",\"ts-train-service\",\"ts-travel-service\"]. For each combination of cmdb_id and kpi_name: (1) compute global P95 and P5 using the full available series of that component-KPI (do NOT filter by incident window before computing these percentiles); (2) then filter that component-KPI series to the incident window 2024-01-23 04:33:01 to 2024-01-23 05:03:01 UTC; (3) in the filtered window, compute: count of points, max value in window, min value in window, count of high anomalies where value >= global_P95, earliest timestamp of a high anomaly (if any), count of low anomalies where value <= global_P5, earliest timestamp of a low anomaly (if any). Return a compact table with rows only for component-KPI pairs that have (high_anomaly_count + low_anomaly_count) > 0. Limit output to top 20 rows. Include columns: cmdb_id, kpi_name, global_p95, global_p5, points_in_window, max_in_window, min_in_window, high_anom_count, first_high_anom_timestamp, low_anom_count, first_low_anom_timestamp. Keep full filtered dataframes in memory for later steps but do not print them." }

